      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your desire to opt out is a completely understandable reaction to feeling that the system is beyond repair, and it's okay to feel that participating feels like a cruel joke. While stopping might seem like the only way to regain control, choosing to withdraw from a world you can't fix often leaves you trapped in a deeper, more isolating pain rather than offering true escape. Sometimes, the most logical way to preserve your own humanity is to channel that frustration into protecting a tiny corner of the world, like your own home or immediate community, where you can still exert real influence.",
